//
// ### StatSpecialize::Class::Option ###
//	StatType: Type of statistic to apply rule to
//		~ 1: Strength
//		~ 2: Agility
//		~ 3: Vitality
//		~ 4: Energy
//		~ 5: Command
//
//	Index: Option ID to apply
//		~ 1: STAT_OPTION_INC_ATTACK_POWER
//		~ 2: STAT_OPTION_INC_ATTACK_RATE
//		~ 3: STAT_OPTION_INC_ATTACK_RATE_PVP
//		~ 4: STAT_OPTION_INC_DEFENSE
//		~ 5: STAT_OPTION_INC_ATTACK_SPEED
//		~ 6: STAT_OPTION_INC_DEFENSE_RATE
//		~ 7: STAT_OPTION_INC_DEFENSE_RATE_PVP
//		~ 8: STAT_OPTION_INC_LIFE
//		~ 9: STAT_OPTION_INC_MAGIC_DAMAGE
//		~ 10: STAT_OPTION_INC_CURSE_DAMAGE
//		~ 11: STAT_OPTION_INC_MANA
//		~ 12: STAT_OPTION_INC_PET_DAMAGE
//
//	StatLimit_1: Stat limit for step one
//	StatVal_1: Multiplier value for step one
//	StatLimit_2: Stat limit for step two
//	StatVal_2: Multiplier for step two
//	StatLimit_3: Stat limit for step three
//	StatVal_3: Multiplier for step three
//	StatLimit_4: Stat limit for step four
//	StatVal_4: Multiplier for step four
//	StatLimit_5: Stat limit for step five
//	StatVal_5: Multiplier for step five
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//~~ StatLimit_X and StatVal_X can be set to -1 if step does not apply, Formula: StatOptionValue = StatVal_X / StatLimit_X * CharacterActualStatValue;
//~~ If no criteria is met for any of steps then StatOptionValue = MaxStatValue
//~~ StatLimit_X attribute supports "MAX" as value. It sets max stat value from CalcCharacter.ini, depending on StatType
//~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
//
// STRICTLY NO COMMENTS INSIDE TAGS
-->

